03/02/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- A NATO advisory team within the BiH Defence Ministry officially launched its activities with a ceremony in Sarajevo on Wednesday (2 February). Under the project, the NATO HQ in BiH was formally moved from Camp Butmir into the ministry's new premises in the Bosnian capital. US Brigadier General Steven P. Schook leads the team. 
In other news Wednesday, members of the BiH State Investigation and Protection Agency searched the premises of the Elektroprivreda Republika Srpska power utility's branch in Trebinje. The operation was carried out at the request of the BiH State Prosecutor's Office.
Meanwhile, Bosnian Serb President Dragan Cavic left for Brussels on Wednesday for meetings with the Peace Implementation Council, a panel tasked with overseeing compliance with the Dayton Peace Accords. The focus will be on Republika Srpska's co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal. (Dnevni avaz, Nezavisne novine - 03/02/05; Fena, PBS BiH, AFP, Pincom.info, RTRS - 02/02/05)
